column1: On each trial of this task, you will see two images on the left and right side of the computer screen, like below.
Your job is to memorize that these images  go together. You can use any strategy to remember this.
For example, you could rehearse them in your memory, or link them through a story.
It's important that you remember that these images go together. Your memory will later be tested.
Each pair of images will only last on the screen for a few sceonds, so pay attention!
Get ready to see a series of image pairs!
When you're ready to start the game, press space!
Great job! Now it's time for the memory test. We willl see how well you remember the pairs.
You will first see one image on the computer screen. Try to bring to mind the associated image pair.
In this situation, you would try to imagine the book.
After you see one of the images, you will see three other images. You should select the correct image pair.
The response options are below each image. In this case, you should press 'J' because the book was paired with the woman, Jessica Alba.
Try to chose the correct response as quickly as you can! Put your right hand on the keyboard and get ready to respond!
These keyboard options will remain on the screen under each image as a reminder throughout the task.
When you're ready to start the game, press space!
